< review>
Foothill Optometric Center does an excellent job for eye care! I have been a patient for 3 years and have found their service both efficient and thorough.  The annual exams include checking both the front and back of the eye followed by a consultation with the doctor to view the images on computer and discuss results.   Staff also advise on selection of frames from a wide range of choices, and perform cleaning & maintenance for glasses already owned.

I highly recommend Foothill Optometric Center for the entire family.<//review>

<time>1498025536676</time><user>111450706673730952587<//user>< review>
I can't believe that I forgot about V-Pot review until I passed by today. Nice spacious place with various seating and big fan of face masks. Waitress speak english and mandarin with a solid tone. No trouble understanding each other for sure. Wait time is not as long if they're five or less people. Proper utensils are provided, but if you need more just raised your hand. My bowl was spicy and hot. It's pretty good for the price, but I know there are better out there. Will try other items with colleagues on next schedule visit.</review>

Just a couple from reasonable travel distance to the office. Also, both Yelp and Google reviews have same posters. I smell Bull$h|t..

I showed up 10 min before scheduled time (like you should) and saw the doctor 30 min after the scheduled time.
When I finally got in, I felt like I was at an auction. He quickly rattled off the basic questions (you allergic to anything, any family history, etc) The whole thing took 10 minutes max. I felt like he just wants to get through as many people as possible in shortest time possible. (same was noted by other 1 star reviewers)
He ordered a handful of standard tests, was never told which labs I can go to.
My last doctor had a normal pace conversation with me, no rush. Explained what tests he wanted to do and why. Gave me options of local labs and their time of operation along with instructions for fasting, etc
I was scheduled to comeback 4 days later at 9 am.
9:05am the office doors were locked and staff was waiting outside saying they have no keys to get in as they are temps.

<gmap_id>0x80c299cce4753ed9:0xc0d9d01d895932b4<//gmap_id><text>I'm not a big fan of going to the doctor. In fact, my last checkup was over 2 years ago. So after incessant nudging from my family I decided to find a doctor. I checked healthgrades and yelp and saw how many positive reviews Dr. Arasheben has. Like you, I've been dissapointed by businesses with positive reviews before - but there was something that struck me about all of the reviews. So many people said that Dr. Arasheben was extremely pleasant and that he listens to your concerns. I figured if at least a few of those people were right it was worth a shot - so I decided to make an appointment.

Unlike so many doctors, Dr. Arasheben believes in using technology. His website allows you to request an appointment and also complete all of the pre-visit paperwork ahead of time so that you don't have to do it on a clipboard in the office (though you can if you want... but why?) I emailed with the office staff a few times and secured an appointment.

Dr. Arasheben's office is simple, clean and unassuming. It's on the bottom floor of an office building in Tarzana with parking in the back. The front desk staff is nice and since I already filled out all of the paperwork I just had to sign a few forms. I was escorted to an exam room within a few minutes.

It was there I first met the doctor. Dr. Arasheben is extremely warm and pleasant. But he's also extremely knowledgable and nonjudgmental. I discussed a few medical issues with him, and he immediately made suggestions that were thoughtful and workable. He sent me for labs and tests, and within a few days I received a call about a potential health issue that we needed to discuss. I booked an appointment with the person who called.

In the subsequent visit, Dr. Arasheben was very thorough and detailed in his explanation, but also assured me that the issue wasn't extremely severe. However, we made a plan to track the issue and answered every question I had.

I've had one subsequent visit to discuss other lab results and my experience was the same. In addition, I emailed the office with a question and received a timely reply.

I suppose we all have different needs from a doctor, but if you're looking for someone who listens, is extremely knowledgable (and up-to-date in medical research) and is very pleasant, then you can't go wrong with Dr. Arasheben.</text>< resp>

< Review>
Hit this location on a Sunday afternoon and found no lines or crowds (making it a little oasis in the city).

Super friendly folks, coffees done right, and lots of seating made our visit a pleasant one.

As other reviewers have noted, there are no plug-in power stations. We weren't in need so it wasn't an issue. There are power pads on the bar.<//Review>
